messages.messageBody:
In a message dated 7/24/1999 7:05:49 AM Eastern Daylight Time,
fuerst@... writes:

> C'mon, everybody, any other ideas?? :-) ;-) :-) Thanks! Susan

I was last in Sarasota when I lived there as a baby, so I can't be much help,
but I do know that there is a well known art school there, Ringling Art
College. I'd bet they have a really good gallery that's open to the public.

I just now looked at one site on-line and it lists some pretty neat stuff.
<A
HREF="http://www.sarasotafl.org/familyfun.html">http://www.sarasotafl.org/fami
lyfun.html
</A> An interactive science center, historical sites, and there's Ringling
Museum of Art :) There's also a museum of the circus, that's got to be fun.
Anyway, it looks like there's plenty of good stuff there. Reading about it
makes me want to revisit my babyhood :)

Priss
